The way Rene Guenon describes the different Hindu schools as each adapting to its environment, local cultural qualities, etc., while expressing the same essence (albeit thus in a more natural way) - this is a good example of Lamarckian evolution. Adapting organism to environment.

On other hand, the way modern academics see the same Hindu schools (judging by their own decadent condition) as battles of ideas, leading to some dying, disappearing, others managing to survive, changing without inherent purpose (random genetic mutations) - that's Darwinism dawg
Which is also why Fr. Seraphim Rose categorized Darwin's evolution as a doctrine of death, as in it all change can only come through organisms dying, failing, suffering defeat.
